text.section:
Preservation of property. It shall be unlawful and a violation of this section for any person to deface, destroy, disfigure, injure, blemish, or vandalize any part of the transit system. Prohibited activities shall include, but not be limited to:


The unauthorized marking of any part of the transit system with spray paint and other marking substances;



The marking of any part of the transit system with graffiti;



The cutting or mutilating of seats on mass transit vehicles; and



The injuring or destruction of any tree, plant or other vegetation located within the transit system.

Soliciting or carrying on business. No person, unless duly authorized in writing by MDTA, shall anywhere on the transit system:


Engage in any business or commercial activity;



Sell, or offer for sale, any merchandise or service;



Solicit any business or trade;



Sing, dance or play any musical instrument.
